# Git commits on main

When the user says **commit** (or asks to save/commit changes):

1. Work on **`main`** only — do not create feature branches or worktrees for commits.
2. Stage relevant changes, commit on `main`, then **`git push origin main`** unless the user explicitly says not to push.
3. Verify with `git status` after commit and after push.

Do not ask whether to use a branch; default is always `main` + push to live.
